WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.390 --> 00:00:03.390
^ - [Voiceover] You'll need 6 months

00:00:03.390 --> 00:00:06.200
^ to see Melbourne properly, but Viator has some great tours

00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:08.350
^ to give you the flavor in just a few days.

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:11.209
^ Here's a few of my favorites.

00:00:13.229 --> 00:00:14.850
^ If you're in Melbourne during winter,

00:00:14.850 --> 00:00:16.830
^ you can't miss the Aussie Rules footy.

00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:18.790
^ Your guide will explain all the rules,

00:00:18.790 --> 00:00:20.790
^ and grab you a beer at halftime.

00:00:20.790 --> 00:00:23.130
^Go Magpies!

00:00:26.300 --> 00:00:27.680
^ Here's a great way to see the city

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.360
^ and enjoy a fabulous meal at the same time.

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:32.582
^ A heads up, though, this tour regularly

00:00:32.582 --> 00:00:34.430
^ sells out weeks in advance.

00:00:34.430 --> 00:00:37.560
^ Read the reviews and you'll see why.

00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:41.070
^ The Yarra Valley is only an hour from town.

00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:43.660
^ On this private guided tour, you see wineries

00:00:43.660 --> 00:00:45.750
^ and beautiful Sherbrooke Forest,

00:00:45.750 --> 00:00:48.840
^ the Dandenong Ranges, and some amazing wildlife,

00:00:48.840 --> 00:00:52.890
^ and there's a great spit roast lunch at Fergusson Winery.

00:00:53.600 --> 00:00:55.800
^ Our Cellar Door Pass is a smartcard that makes you

00:00:55.800 --> 00:00:58.350
^ and your partner a special guest at dozens of wineries

00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:01.800
all over the state with lots of extra benefits.

00:01:01.800 --> 00:01:04.240
^ Another way to see the Yarra Valley is to combine a wineries

00:01:04.240 --> 00:01:07.821
^ tour with a ride through Sherbrooke Forest on Puffing Billy.

00:01:07.821 --> 00:01:09.155
^ Whether you've brought the kids or not,

00:01:09.155 --> 00:01:11.610
this is a heap of fun.

00:01:12.590 --> 00:01:15.150
^ Just after dark every night, the world's smallest penguins

00:01:15.150 --> 00:01:18.320
^ waddle home after spending the day at sea fishing.

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:20.800
^ It's an amazing scene, and our Ultimate Penguin Experience

00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:24.090
^ tour is a great way to see the show.

00:01:25.950 --> 00:01:27.290
^ If you love rugged coastlines,

00:01:27.290 --> 00:01:29.230
^ you'll love the Great Ocean Road.

00:01:29.230 --> 00:01:31.630
^ Our award-winning tour is one photo opportunity

00:01:31.630 --> 00:01:34.170
^ after another, whether it's the 12 Apostles,

00:01:34.170 --> 00:01:37.080
^ the koalas, or the Shipwreck Coast.

00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:39.110
^ But there are no koalas or beaches

00:01:39.110 --> 00:01:40.790
^ or shipwrecks on this tour.

00:01:40.790 --> 00:01:42.800
^ It's three hours of casual meandering

00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:45.493
^ through Melbourne's famous lanes and arcades,

00:01:45.493 --> 00:01:48.210
^ shopping, eating, sipping coffee, and getting

00:01:48.210 --> 00:01:53.210
^ to see deep inside a city most visitors only skim.

00:01:53.960 --> 00:01:55.220
^ That's the thing about Melbourne.

00:01:55.220 --> 00:01:59.343
^ It's got so many sides, sport, cuisine, nature, shopping.

00:01:59.343 --> 00:02:01.070
^ You won't have time to take it all in,

00:02:01.070 --> 00:02:03.385
^ but check out the Melbourne pages on viator.com

00:02:03.385 --> 00:02:05.470
^ and plan some of it today.

00:02:05.470 --> 00:02:08.110
^ See you at the footy!

